Trajectory file (binary):

   Header:

      nAtom int
      headerFormat - bitfield indicating which optional info follows. 
                  Flags: hasSpecies, hasAtomsHeader, hasMoleculesHeader
      [SPECIES] - nMolecule & nAtom per molecule, iff isMolecular 
      [ATOMS] - Format, followed by per atom data
               atomFormat - hasType, hasMass, hasCharge, n = nOptInt, m = nOptreal
               id, typeId, [mass], [charge], nx[optInt], mx[optReal]
      [MOLECULES] - Format (nOptInt, nOptReal). For each molecule id, optional info.

   Frame:

      iStep
      boundary
      nAtom int
      frameFormat - bitfield with flags that include: isMolecular,
                    isOrdered, hasShift, hasVelocity, hasCharge, 
                    hasMolecule, nOptInt, nOptReal
      For each atom (id, position, optionally shift, velocity)
      hasMoleculeData
      if hasMoleculeData
         nOptInt, nOptReal
         For each species( For each molecule (id, optional data))

Trajectory frame format:

   FRAME:
     For each atom {
        id position (scaled, as 3xuint) [shift 3 x small int] [velocity]
     }

